== Prep ==

Zest the @lime{1} then chop into wedges. Roughly chop the @medium tomato{2}. 
Halve the @yellow pepper{1}(halved and cores removed) and @green pepper{1}(halved 
and cores removed). Chop into small pieces. Trim the @spring onion{1} and finely 
slice.

Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all). Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1} 
in a #sieve{}.

== Turkey Steaks ==

Pop the lime zest, half the @ground cumin{2} (reserve half), half the 
@ground coriander{1} (reserve half) and half the @smoked paprika{1} (reserve 
half) in a #mixing bowl{} with a squeeze of lime juice and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. 
Add the @British turkey steaks{2} and coat well using your hands. Pop the steaks 
on a #foil-lined tray{} and grill, ~{10-12%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: The turkey is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Chilli Beans ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large saucepan{} on medium heat.

Add the tomato, peppers, remaining ground cumin, ground coriander and smoked 
paprika, half the spring onion and a pinch of @chilli flakes{¼}. Cook, stirring 
occasionally, until the peppers start to soften, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Pour in the @water{100} and stir in the mixed beans. Bring to the boil then reduce 
the heat and simmer until thick and tomatoey, ~{6-8%minutes}.

== Rice ==

Meanwhile, cook the @steamed brown basmati rice{1} according to pack instructions.

== To Serve ==

When the turkey steaks are cooked, transfer to a #board{} and cut into 4 slices. 
Stir any turkey juices into the chilli beans. Season to taste with @salt{} and 
@pepper{} if needed and stir through half the coriander.

Serve the rice in #bowls{}, topped with the chilli beans and turkey. Finish 
with a sprinkling of remaining coriander, spring onion, chilli flakes (if liked) 
and lime wedges. Enjoy!